    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "What happens here is that when `SIGNAL_COMMUNITIES_UPDATE` is emited, `communityEdited(..)` method in `module.nim` is called and that method creates a new community item instead of updating the existing one and the new item active property is set by default to false (see `createCommunityItem(..)` method). So, when `setActiveSection(..)` in `section_model.nim` is called (when user clicks to another section from ui), the community section that suposed to be active is not so, no `dataChanged(..)` need to be raised. \n\nSame issue happens when editing, for example, the community name since `communityEdited(..)` method is called (new community item created and set as active false).\n\nIn order to fix that, `active` property value in `createCommunityItem(..)` has been set depending on if the current active section corresponds with the item we are going to create. However, I'm wondering if that `createCommunityItem(..)` should be renamed to `updateCommunityItem(..)` and instead of creating a new item instance, it should be necessary to modify the existing one with the new values.",
